  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "From Alexandria
    Stoic philosopher, grammarian and Hellenized Egyptian priest in Alexandria (1st cent. AD). He was appointed tutor to the 
    young Nero. C. was a professor of grammar in Alexandria and probably took part in the Alexandrian delegation to Rome under 
    Emperor Claudius (AD 40). He wrote a ‘History of Egypt, which probably contained his explanations of the hieroglyphs and 
    the Egyptian priesthood..." Inwood, Brad (Toronto). "Chaeremon." Brill’s New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: 
    Hubert Cancik and , Helmuth Schneider. Brill Online, 2014. Reference. Tufts University. 24 February 2014</mads:note>
